hopobject.body: I read a lot www.mobergpharma.se When in search of shellfish, there could hardly be a more idyllic time and place than early morning low tide on Cape Cod. Locals with four-wheel trucks (and beach parking permits) drive right onto the tidal flats and sunbathe, jog and drink beers in the mellow sun. Oyster lovers know to head straight for East Dennis Oyster Farm, which is one of the only oyster farms in the region that's licensed for direct-to-consumer sales. You can get fresh-from-the-sea oysters for $1 apiece â a gourmand's dream.
